Sentencas: Agglomeration of the metal electrode decreases the performance of low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFC) during operation at elevated temperatures.
Titulo: Ridge-Valley Nanostructured Samaria-Doped Ceria Interlayer for Thermally Stable Cathode Interface in Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Here, we report a Pt electrode/ridge-valley nanostructured samaria-doped ceria (SDC) layer interface with extended lifetime.
Titulo: Ridge-Valley Nanostructured Samaria-Doped Ceria Interlayer for Thermally Stable Cathode Interface in Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: LT-SOFCs with RF-sputtered SDC interlayers with thicknesses in the range 65-260nm show a >20 times lower degradation of performance as compared to cells without interlayer when operated at 450 degrees C (1.8%h(-1) vs. 45%h(-1)).
Titulo: Ridge-Valley Nanostructured Samaria-Doped Ceria Interlayer for Thermally Stable Cathode Interface in Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Micromorphological analysis reveals that the coarsening of the Pt electrode is significantly suppressed by the presence of the nanostructured SDC interlayer, possibly due to a stronger bonding between this layer and the Pt grains.
Titulo: Ridge-Valley Nanostructured Samaria-Doped Ceria Interlayer for Thermally Stable Cathode Interface in Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
